{
  "text": "Another branch learns to detect local sub-text components which are independent from the whole text [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . SegLink [CITATION_4] proposes to detect components, i.e. square areas that are text, and how these components are linked to each other. PixelLink [CITATION_5] predicts which pixels belong to any text and whether adjacent pixels belong to the same text instances. Corner localization [CITATION_6] detects text corners. All these methods learn to detect local components and then group them together to make final detections.",
